-- Chinalco Hires Dredging International for Peru Pier, Andina Says
-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   E m e r y
-- 2011-12-26T16:56:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-26/chinalco-hires-dredging-international-for-peru-pier-andina-says.html
An Aluminum Corp. of China-led group
hired  Belgium ’s  Dredging International NV  to begin work at its
$130 million minerals pier project in  Lima ,  Peru ’s state news
agency  Andina  reported.  Aluminum Corp., together with partners Glencore
International AG and Trafigura Beheer NV, will start
construction work on the pier in Lima’s port of Callao in April
and start operating it in the second half of 2013, Andina said,
citing Frank Boyle, president of Peru’s  National Port Authority .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Carlos Caminada at 
